# Documentation on change (required)

When you **change app behavior**, **add a feature**, **add/alter a migration**, or **change user-visible UX**, update documentation in the **same task** (same PR/commit). Do not ship code-only unless the user explicitly asks to skip docs.

## Minimum checklist

1. **Identify impact** — UI, RPC/DB, settings, tests, deploy.
2. **Update mapped docs** (below) — remove stale text (e.g. removed UI, old flows).
3. **Migrations** — add step to `app/supabase/README.txt`; note in `docs/backend/phase1-use-cases-and-tests.md` pre-flight if tests need it.
4. **Changelog** — one bullet in `docs/LLM_CONTEXT.md` (newest first, date + what changed).
5. **Tests** — extend `app/scripts/e2e-*.mjs` when behavior is testable in source/live checks.
6. **Manual QA** — add/adjust rows in `docs/backend/phase1-manual-e2e-checklist.md` for new screens or flows.

## Doc map (what to touch)

| Change type | Update |
|-------------|--------|
| New SQL migration | `app/supabase/README.txt`, `docs/backend/data-model.md`, `docs/backend/phase1-use-cases-and-tests.md` |
| Purchase / supplier invoice / VAT | `docs/PURCHASE_REFERENCE_NUMBERS.md`, `data-model.md` (purchases/products pricing) |
| Product pricing / catalog | `docs/backend/data-model.md` (products), manual checklist § Products |
| Settings / tenant fields | `data-model.md` (`tenant_settings`), manual checklist § Settings |
| Sales bill / print / PDF | `docs/backend/data-model.md` (sales), `phase1-use-cases` if maths/RPC |
| New route or major page | `docs/LLM_CONTEXT.md` (routes/features), manual checklist if user-facing |
| GTM / pricing / ICP / positioning | `docs/GTM_NEPAL.md` (open questions + revision log) |
| Deferred / future work only | `docs/DEFERRED_WORK.md` or `BACKEND-TODO.md` — not LLM_CONTEXT unless shipped |
| New `npm run e2e:*` script | `docs/backend/phase1-use-cases-and-tests.md`, project `README.md` if user-facing |

Hub index: `docs/README.md` — add a link when you add a new top-level doc.

## Style

- Match existing doc tone: short tables, links to migrations runbook.
- Document **what users see** and **what DB stores** when they differ (e.g. buy excl. in UI, incl. in `purchase_price`).
